Cell["\<\
Contour plots allow you to represent three dimensional data in two \
dimensional surfaces using contour lines, which connect points of equal \
value. Examples include topographical maps and electric potential graphs.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7319350243250074`*^9, 3.731935029417118*^9}, {
  3.7319350933097367`*^9, 3.73193509391383*^9}, {3.795122802427187*^9, 
