  3.9404171790883446`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"238c8a8c-9ac0-4d8d-a0cd-\
e0bf891100b1"],

Cell["\<\
RegionPlot is a function allowing you to visualize regions that satisfy \
inequalities or conditions in two variables. This could be useful in \
displaying solution sets, feasible regions or any example needing a clear \
picture where conditions hold true in a coordinate plane.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7319350243250074`*^9, 3.731935029417118*^9}, {
  3.7319350933097367`*^9, 3.73193509391383*^9}, {3.795122802427187*^9, 
  3.7951228032882195`*^9}, {3.9404161988597317`*^9, 3.940416229189071*^9}, {
  3.9404164475016823`*^9, 3.9404164475036793`*^9}, {3.9404171744249983`*^9, 
  3.9404173101671295`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fd01b6b0-18cb-4664-8140-\
e2bd464a0e05"],

Cell["", "Text",
